race.comment: MADE EASY (3) not that far away when fifth over 1100m at Gundagai. That followed a win on debut at Wagga. Looking for the trip and has the ability to figure prominently. SWIFT GUN (1) resumes from a spell of four-and-a-half months and now in the Danielle Seib yard. Had mixed luck in four runs on the provincial tracks last time in. Back without a trial and gets his chance. MY INSPIRATION (8) accounted for a maiden field in good style over 1400m at Gundagai. Looks up to this tougher task from the inside gate. Each way. MARITIME EXPRESS (4) sound return when a commanding winner over 1200m at Nowra. Sticky draw today, and Nick Heywood retains the ride. Stays in the mix. SUMMER NIGHT (7) big drop in weight after disappointing as fav when seventh over 1476m at Penshurst. Assess on his earlier runs.
